1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,914
This is the data scientist version of the zero-shot coastal bacteria result.

2
00:00:05,914 --> 00:00:12,321
It walks through the panel contract, PI feature engine, model protocol, nulls, gates

3
00:00:12,321 --> 00:00:13,800
washouts, and limitations.

4
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:23,594
The research question was narrow: can a label-free model train on non-target basins and rank enterococcus exceedance in a completely held-out basin

5
00:00:23,594 --> 00:00:27,600
with zero target-domain labels or lab-history features as inputs?

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:36,341
The final scored panel had twelve domains, 708,337 held-out rows, and 57,628 events.

7
00:00:36,341 --> 00:00:44,410
Rows needed a date, site, basin, coordinates, a comparable daily bacteria label

8
00:00:44,410 --> 00:00:47,100
and finite PI features.

9
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:51,848
Data quality was enforced by exclusion, not wishful imputation.

10
00:00:51,848 --> 00:00:56,597
Empty Wales, annual-only EEA bathing class data, pre-2012 Montenegro

11
00:00:56,597 --> 00:01:02,400
and Hong Kong without coordinates were excluded from daily PI transfer.

12
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:07,470
The anti-leak feature contract allowed weather, PI groups, calendar

13
00:01:07,470 --> 00:01:11,977
optional geography, and optional strings for non-headline arms.

14
00:01:11,977 --> 00:01:17,610
It blocked FIB concentration, hazard labels, exceedance labels, lab-history lags

15
00:01:17,610 --> 00:01:19,300
and target-domain labels.

16
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:25,848
The headline feature set was five PI groups: Damkohler-style decay, loading, UV dose

17
00:01:25,848 --> 00:01:27,863
Peclet-style transport, and flushing.

18
00:01:27,863 --> 00:01:32,900
These are shared physical coordinates rather than basin identity features.

19
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:40,476
We also engineered compact label-free physics kernels from the same inputs: decay-adjusted load

20
00:01:40,476 --> 00:01:45,721
solar survival load, runoff memory, first flush, flushing inverse

21
00:01:45,721 --> 00:01:49,800
spring-neap exchange, transport retention, and wind resuspension.

22
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:55,457
The model zoo compared calendar, PI, PI plus calendar, raw physics

23
00:01:55,457 --> 00:02:00,086
physics plus geography, physics-kernel variants, and sampled CARTE strings.

24
00:02:00,086 --> 00:02:04,200
The frozen public winner was PI plus logistic.

25
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,441
The validation split was leave-one-basin-out.

26
00:02:06,441 --> 00:02:12,269
For each target, the model trained only on rows from the other basins

27
00:02:12,269 --> 00:02:14,510
then scored the hidden basin.

28
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:17,200
This repeated across all twelve domains.

29
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:19,581
The primary metric was average precision

30
00:02:19,581 --> 00:02:23,152
because the use case is ranking early sampling attention.

31
00:02:23,152 --> 00:02:29,500
The base-rate baseline is the held-out event rate; lift is AP divided by that base rate.

32
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,955
The null check was source-stratum permutation.

33
00:02:31,955 --> 00:02:35,636
Outcomes were shuffled within source buckets, preserving source mix

34
00:02:35,636 --> 00:02:40,545
and the real AP had to beat the ninety-fifth percentile shuffled score.

35
00:02:40,545 --> 00:02:43,000
It did on all twelve targets.

36
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,722
The freeze gate required every target above base rate

37
00:02:46,722 --> 00:02:50,030
at least eighty percent above the permutation null

38
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:53,338
at least one hundred null draws per target

39
00:02:53,338 --> 00:02:58,300
AP-minus-base bootstrap lower bound above zero, and mean-lift lower bound above one.

40
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:09,244
The headline PI plus logistic result was mean AP 0.1511 versus mean base rate 0.0909

41
00:03:09,244 --> 00:03:12,163
for mean lift 1.752.

42
00:03:12,163 --> 00:03:18,000
The domain-bootstrap AP-minus-base interval was 0.0365 to 0.086.

43
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,403
Per-target results were not one lucky basin.

44
00:03:21,403 --> 00:03:25,778
All twelve held-out domains beat their own base rate.

45
00:03:25,778 --> 00:03:30,639
The strongest lifts were Australia New South Wales, California, Ireland

46
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:35,500
and Texas; the weakest lift was North Carolina at 1.186.

47
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:39,618
The richer physics-kernel arms looked tempting on mean AP

48
00:03:39,618 --> 00:03:42,821
but they washed under the promotion rule.

49
00:03:42,821 --> 00:03:46,024
The best kernel added 0.0083 mean AP

50
00:03:46,024 --> 00:03:50,600
but its paired-domain interval crossed zero and five targets regressed.

51
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:53,607
CARTE and entity-string variants were not frozen.

52
00:03:53,607 --> 00:03:58,333
Prior same-sample fair-baseline checks failed, and full-panel CARTE was too slow

53
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:02,200
so strings did not become part of the claim.

54
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,690
The limitations matter.

55
00:04:03,690 --> 00:04:07,167
This is a retrospective zero-shot ranking screen

56
00:04:07,167 --> 00:04:09,650
not a calibrated advisory probability.

57
00:04:09,650 --> 00:04:17,100
Persistence and seasonal-naive were not run because target-domain history is forbidden in the cold-start setting.

58
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:21,378
The reproducibility artifacts are the runner, markdown and JSON outputs

59
00:04:21,378 --> 00:04:23,517
freeze manifest, and test file.

60
00:04:23,517 --> 00:04:32,500
The caveat is that byte-reproduction from a clean clone is not yet proven because cached panels are not public frozen inputs.

61
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:45,000
The defensible data-science claim is narrow: a simple PI plus logistic ranker clears a hardened zero-shot screen for prioritizing early sampling in unseen coastal bacteria basins.
